    "documentation": "# ZohoCRM\n\n## Overview\n\nThe ZohoCRM node allows you to connect your application with Zoho CRM to automate tasks such as managing leads, contacts, accounts, deals, campaigns, and more. It helps streamline sales workflows by enabling seamless integration with your CRM data.\n\n## Authentication Ways\n\n- OAuth 2.0 <a href=\"https://www.zoho.com/crm/developer/docs/api/oauth-overview.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Documentation</a>\n\n## OAuth 2.0\n\nTo use the ZohoCRM node, you need to authenticate using OAuth 2.0. Follow the steps below to set up your OAuth credentials and authorize access to your Zoho CRM data.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Connect via Boltic**\n\n   - Enter the **name** of your integration in the required field\n\n2. **Authorize Access**\n\n   - Click **Connect** or **Authorize**\n   - You will be redirected to Zoho's login and consent screen\n   - Log in using your Zoho credentials\n   - Grant access when prompted\n   - Once the button turns green, click **Save** â€” your credentials are now securely stored in Boltic\n\n3. **Token Handling**\n   - After successful authentication, Boltic will store both the **access token** and **refresh token** securely\n   - Tokens will be refreshed automatically when expired\n\nFor more details, see the <a href=\"https://www.zoho.com/crm/developer/docs/api/v8/api-collection.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span> Custom API Documentation</span></a>\n",
